docs.abstract: British regulators cited the newness of the cloud gaming field to block Microsoft’s $69 billion acquisition of Activision, a shift in antitrust strategy.
docs.snippet: British regulators cited the newness of the cloud gaming field to block Microsoft’s $69 billion acquisition of Activision, a shift in antitrust strategy.
docs.lead_paragraph: As companies like Google and Facebook grew into giants in the early 21st century, regulators chose largely not to interfere in the still-young market for online services.

headline.main: As Regulators Block Tech Deals, They Increasingly Look to the Future
headline.print_headline: Regulators Have New Focus in Assessing Tech Deals: The Future

byline.original: By David McCabe and Kellen Browning

docs.abstract: A former S.E.C. chief and a former White House economics chief on how progressive regulators are outsourcing U.S. regulatory policy to Europe.
docs.snippet: A former S.E.C. chief and a former White House economics chief on how progressive regulators are outsourcing U.S. regulatory policy to Europe.
docs.lead_paragraph: Congress has given federal regulators broad authority over key areas of our society, and the actions of those regulators often have profound effects on our lives and on our future. We applaud the swift and decisive actions by financial regulators to prevent the run on Silicon Valley Bank from cascading through the regional banking system. But regulatory power is not absolute; it is granted by Congress and has strict limits, and its exercise requires due process.

headline.main: The Microsoft-Activision Mess Is a Blow to American Sovereignty
headline.print_headline: The U.S. Is Outsourcing Policy to Europe

byline.original: By Jay Clayton and Gary D. Cohn

docs.abstract: The tech giant is sprinting to protect its core business with a flurry of projects, including updates to its search engine and plans for an all-new one.
docs.snippet: The tech giant is sprinting to protect its core business with a flurry of projects, including updates to its search engine and plans for an all-new one.
docs.lead_paragraph: Google’s employees were shocked when they learned in March that the South Korean consumer electronics giant Samsung was considering replacing Google with Microsoft’s Bing as the default search engine on its devices.

docs.abstract: The decision barring the takeover of a big video game publisher is a major victory for proponents of regulating tech giants, which have faced obstacles in the United States.
docs.snippet: The decision barring the takeover of a big video game publisher is a major victory for proponents of regulating tech giants, which have faced obstacles in the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: British antitrust regulators dealt a major setback on Wednesday to Microsoft’s plans to acquire the video game giant Activision Blizzard for $69 billion, blocking the proposed deal and handing a notable win to government enforcers around the world who want to rein in Big Tech.

headline.main: U.K. Blocks Microsoft’s $69 Billion Bid for Activision, a Blow for Tech Deals

docs.abstract: Dominion Voting Systems’ lawsuit against Fox News won’t start on Monday, as Rupert Murdoch’s media colossus reportedly pushes for an out-of-court settlement.
docs.snippet: Dominion Voting Systems’ lawsuit against Fox News won’t start on Monday, as Rupert Murdoch’s media colossus reportedly pushes for an out-of-court settlement.
docs.lead_paragraph: Monday was to be the start of the biggest defamation trial in recent American history — but opening proceedings in Dominion Voting Systems’ lawsuit against Fox News over on-air remarks about the 2020 election were delayed by a day.

headline.main: The Defamation Trial of the Century Is Delayed

docs.abstract: The troubled lender is working on a lifeline, but time is running out.
docs.snippet: The troubled lender is working on a lifeline, but time is running out.
docs.lead_paragraph: First Republic is limping into the weekend, days after reporting disastrous first-quarter results. The bank is still working on a lifeline, with some involved saying it is touch and go whether the federal government will assist in some way, DealBook hears.

headline.main: First Republic’s Troubles Reignite Fears of a Banking Crisis

docs.abstract: The British antitrust watchdog blocked the takeover attempt, in a decision that will be closely watched in Washington and Brussels.
docs.snippet: The British antitrust watchdog blocked the takeover attempt, in a decision that will be closely watched in Washington and Brussels.
docs.lead_paragraph: Britain’s mergers regulator on Wednesday blocked Microsoft’s $69 billion takeover bid for Activision Blizzard, ruling that buying the maker of “Call of Duty” would give the tech giant too much control of the thriving market for cloud-based video games.

headline.main: The U.K. Deals a Huge Blow to Microsoft’s $69 Billion Activision Bid

docs.abstract: Technology companies were once leery of what some artificial intelligence could do. Now the priority is winning control of the industry’s next big thing.
docs.snippet: Technology companies were once leery of what some artificial intelligence could do. Now the priority is winning control of the industry’s next big thing.
docs.lead_paragraph: In March, two Google employees, whose jobs are to review the company’s artificial intelligence products, tried to stop Google from launching an A.I. chatbot. They believed it generated inaccurate and dangerous statements.

headline.main: In A.I. Race, Microsoft and Google Choose Speed Over Caution
